The #USCMA isn’t a partisan victory important to only Republicans or Democrats; it’s important to America. Passage of this trade agreement is long overdue. I’m ready to get into the business of doing things together, getting bills signed into law, and making a difference for our constituents. pic.twitter.com/8nRwca1TZI

Download the FEMA App for preparedness tips, shelter information, and weather alerts. You also can visit  http://Ready.gov  for more information on what you can do ahead of this dangerous storm. (7/7)
Each year, more deaths occur due to flooding than from any other severe weather-related hazard. DO NOT walk, swim, or drive through flood waters. (6/7)

Residents in Georgia should visit  http://GEMA.Georgia.gov  or call (404) 635-7000 for the latest in evacuation and storm information. Before evacuating, fill up your gas tank, stock your vehicle with emergency supplies, and know your evacuation routes. (5/7)

Georgia issued mandatory evacuations and contraflow of Interstate 16 began at 8 AM TODAY. A mandatory evacuation order is in effect for individuals living east of I-95 in Bryan, Camden, Chatham, Glynn, Liberty, and McIntosh Counties due to Hurricane Dorian. (4/7)
Storm tracks can change rapidly – those in the potential impact areas should continue to pay attention to Dorian’s forecast. If you are told to evacuate, DO NOT TOUGH IT OUT, GET OUT. (3/7)
Life-threatening storm surge and hurricane-force winds began along #Florida’s east coast last night, and are expected along the coasts of #Georgia, #SouthCarolina and #NorthCarolina this week. (2/7)

#Dorian Thread:

As #HurricaneDorian’s path over the next few days remains uncertain, @FEMA urges residents and visitors along the southeastern coast of the U.S. to complete preparations, monitor the storm closely, and follow instructions and warnings of local officials. (1/7)
